WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:24.600
The Lost Ship by Stephen Coleborn Sunday 5th of December 1872.

00:24.600 --> 00:31.680
The weather is fine, the wind is blowing and the ship is sailing quickly.

00:31.680 --> 00:38.160
The men are happy, we are sailing between Cuba and Florida.

00:38.160 --> 00:41.360
We are going to be in Florida soon.

00:41.360 --> 00:51.360
We are going to reach Florida in three or four days.

00:51.360 --> 00:57.560
This is the captain of the ship, he is in his cabin.

00:57.560 --> 01:01.840
He is writing in the ship's log book.

01:01.840 --> 01:07.000
The captain writes in the log book every day.

01:07.000 --> 01:12.520
He writes about the weather and he writes about the ship.

01:12.520 --> 01:17.520
He also writes about the men on the ship.

01:17.520 --> 01:20.600
The ship is old.

01:20.600 --> 01:23.640
It is a sailing ship.

01:23.640 --> 01:29.000
The wind blows and the ship sails.

01:29.000 --> 01:33.840
The captain and his men are going home.

01:33.840 --> 01:37.680
They are going to reach home soon.

01:37.680 --> 01:41.760
They are well and happy.

01:41.760 --> 01:46.320
Captain, there is a strange ship near us.

01:46.320 --> 01:54.520
Can you come on deck?

01:54.520 --> 01:59.400
Now the captain and all the men are on deck.

01:59.400 --> 02:03.080
They are looking at the strange ship.

02:03.080 --> 02:06.440
It is a very strange ship.

02:06.440 --> 02:09.200
There is no name on the ship.

02:09.200 --> 02:12.280
There are no men on deck.

02:12.280 --> 02:15.120
Where are the ships men?

02:15.120 --> 02:17.600
The captain is shouting.

02:17.600 --> 02:19.400
Hello?

02:19.400 --> 02:22.040
Is anybody there?

02:22.040 --> 02:24.440
Can you hear me?

02:24.440 --> 02:27.640
Is anybody there?

02:27.640 --> 02:32.880
But there is no answer from the strange ship.

02:32.880 --> 02:35.520
Where are the men on the ship?

02:35.520 --> 02:42.400
Are they ill?

02:42.400 --> 02:46.640
The captain gets into a small boat.

02:46.640 --> 02:50.760
Two men go in the boat with him.

02:50.760 --> 02:55.400
They row across to the strange ship.

02:55.400 --> 03:01.080
They are going to look for the men on the ship.

03:01.080 --> 03:06.040
The captain is on the deck of the strange ship.

03:06.040 --> 03:09.480
The two men are with him.

03:09.480 --> 03:12.920
They walk along the deck.

03:12.920 --> 03:17.160
They go to the ship's wheel.

03:17.160 --> 03:20.960
There is nobody at the wheel.

03:20.960 --> 03:24.720
Nobody is steering the ship.

03:24.720 --> 03:28.320
The ship is sailing in the wind.

03:28.320 --> 03:32.640
The wind is steering the ship.

03:32.640 --> 03:35.040
The captain shouts.

03:35.040 --> 03:38.920
Is anybody here?

03:38.920 --> 03:41.480
There is no answer.

03:41.480 --> 03:50.000
There is nobody on deck.

03:50.000 --> 03:53.200
The captain is below deck.

03:53.200 --> 03:56.600
He is looking for the ship's men.

03:56.600 --> 04:01.000
He cannot find them.

04:01.000 --> 04:05.280
Now he is in the cabin where the men eat.

04:05.280 --> 04:08.200
There is a table.

04:08.200 --> 04:11.600
There is food on the table.

04:11.600 --> 04:15.880
But who is going to eat the food?

04:15.880 --> 04:18.720
There is water in the jug.

04:18.720 --> 04:23.280
But who is going to drink the water?

04:23.280 --> 04:27.120
There is a cigar in the ashtray.

04:27.120 --> 04:33.880
But who is smoking the cigar?

04:33.880 --> 04:37.040
This is the captain's cabin.

04:37.040 --> 04:40.440
The captain is not here.

04:40.440 --> 04:44.520
There is nobody in the cabin.

04:44.520 --> 04:48.520
There is a table and a chair.

04:48.520 --> 04:54.440
The ship's logbook and a photograph are on the table.

04:54.440 --> 04:56.400
The ship's logbook is open.

04:59.400 --> 05:05.280
Thursday, 25th of November, 1869.

05:05.280 --> 05:07.440
Where are we?

05:07.440 --> 05:11.080
Somewhere in the Atlantic Ocean?

05:11.080 --> 05:15.320
Somewhere between Bermuda and Florida?

05:15.320 --> 05:17.560
I don't know.

05:17.560 --> 05:21.680
The ship is in a thick white mist.

05:21.680 --> 05:26.200
I cannot see the sun or stars.

05:26.200 --> 05:28.680
There is no wind.

05:28.680 --> 05:32.320
The ship is not moving.

05:32.320 --> 05:36.560
Every day I pray for wind.

05:36.560 --> 05:40.080
When will the wind come?

05:40.080 --> 05:42.920
The men are angry.

05:42.920 --> 05:46.080
They want to leave the ship.

05:46.080 --> 05:49.880
They want to take the small boat.

05:49.880 --> 05:53.640
They want to row to Florida.

05:53.640 --> 05:57.400
They want to go home.

05:57.400 --> 06:03.160
Friday, 26th of November, 1869.

06:03.160 --> 06:06.480
The men are getting into the small boat.

06:06.480 --> 06:10.360
They are going to row to Florida.

06:10.360 --> 06:16.040
Saturday, 27th of November, 1869.

06:16.040 --> 06:18.320
I am alone.

06:18.320 --> 06:22.200
I am waiting for the wind.

06:22.200 --> 06:25.360
The captain reads the logbook.

06:25.360 --> 06:28.680
He sees the photograph on the table.

06:28.680 --> 06:30.880
He picks it up.

06:30.880 --> 06:33.680
He looks at the photograph.

06:33.680 --> 06:35.560
No.

06:35.560 --> 06:36.960
No, it can't be.

06:42.600 --> 06:46.160
The captain looks at the photograph.

06:46.160 --> 06:49.920
It is a photograph of a man.

06:49.920 --> 06:54.680
The captain looks in the mirror on the cabin wall.

06:54.680 --> 06:58.240
He looks at his face in the mirror.

06:58.240 --> 07:02.560
He looks at the face in the photograph.

07:02.560 --> 07:05.600
They are the same.

07:05.600 --> 07:07.560
It is a photograph of himself.

07:12.200 --> 07:15.720
The captain runs up on deck.

07:15.720 --> 07:20.240
There is a thick white mist around the ship.

07:20.240 --> 07:23.040
The captain looks around.

07:23.040 --> 07:25.760
He can see nobody.

07:25.760 --> 07:29.160
He can see nothing.

07:29.160 --> 07:31.680
Where is his ship?

07:31.680 --> 07:34.680
Where are his men?

07:34.680 --> 07:37.840
He cannot see the sun.

07:37.840 --> 07:41.280
He is alone.

07:41.280 --> 07:44.480
I do not know the date.

07:44.480 --> 07:46.560
Where am I?

07:46.560 --> 07:49.360
I do not know.

07:49.360 --> 07:52.360
I am the captain of this ship.

07:52.360 --> 07:55.520
I must sail the ship.

07:55.520 --> 07:58.280
Where am I going?

07:58.280 --> 08:00.840
I do not know.

08:00.840 --> 08:03.280
What is my name?

08:03.280 --> 08:06.840
What is the name of this ship?

08:06.840 --> 08:09.760
I do not know.

08:09.760 --> 08:12.400
I am waiting.

08:12.400 --> 08:15.720
Another ship is going to come.

08:15.720 --> 08:20.160
Another captain is going to take my place.

08:20.160 --> 08:23.400
Then I can rest.

08:23.400 --> 08:25.400
I am waiting.

